name: Aztec restoration #3
description: Detail from plate 72 of the 16th century aztec Codex Borgia, part of a plate showing the four directions and the deities associated with them. This plate shows the deity of the south, Macuilxochitl, a god of pleasure, inebriation and excessive consumption. He has the trecana day signs of Lizard, Rabbit, Grass, Vulture and Flower attached to his body. A clawed feathered serpent forms the border of the page.
